data.title: What is it like to be a high ranking senior Asian officer in the U.S. Armed Forces?
data.meta_description:
Answer (1 of 4): GEN Eric Shinseki Retired was one such officer.

He was my Division Commander at Fort Hood in the 94 and 95. He was very well regarded and respected. He went on to be the Army Chief of Staff. (Highest position in the Army)
